geometry.note: Separations < window_len are excluded to avoid A/B/C overlap artifacts.

mux.chip: PRN chips derived from sha256(code) (non-constant, deterministic)
mux.msg: exogenous msg(t) from repo weights bits; bit_hold=25, lpf_beta=0.01
mux.metric: rho_X = safe_corr( env_X_resid, (msg_resid * chip_X) ); delta = rho_B - rho_C
mux.instrumentation: safe_corr returns NaN on zero-variance; aggregates use nanmedian; std_* diagnostics included.
mux.note: Engineered comms baseline; no physics/biology claim.

definitions.goal: Selective listening: B (matching code) decodes message better than C (mismatch) at equal distance under a shared broadcast carrier.
non_claims: Engineered spread-spectrum + matched filtering baseline, not entanglement, not biology.
